Chapter 2
Title: A pure love

                                  Disclaimer: I don't own nothing...damn
:                    ***Benji's P.O.V***
 My eyes flutter open only to be met with Joel's dark fuzzy hair.
Chuckling lightly I gently place his head on the pillow so I don't wake him up. 
The empty space in my stomach is becoming more and more noticeable to me until I have to go get something to eat.
I take a quick glance at the clock and find that me and Joel had slept for 6 hours.
Not bad.
After throwing some pants on I run downstairs to find some nourishment.
I look through the cereal cabinet but find nothing that interests me all that much, so I move on to the freezer.
Five minutes later my frozen waffle pops up from the toaster and into my hand.
I sit down at the table with my breakfast, now covered in syrup, and munch away.
Not long after, I hear feet padding softly across the linoleum flooring of the kitchen.
Once again I am met with the feeling of eyes on me.
I look up to see Joel staring intently at me and that makes me curious.
"Can I help you?" I say getting slightly annoyed.
"Huh?" "Oh sorry" he says in such a soft voice I can hardly even hear it.
"You okay Joely?" 
He looks at me and before he even answers I know he is lying.
"yea fine"
Call it a twin sense or exp but I can read Joel like a book, most of the time.
There are times when Joel shuts me out. 
It hurts me when he does this, not too deeply, I understand we need or secrets, but I would still rather have him tell me everything.
"Joel" I say giving him the look our mother gives us when we cuss.
He sighs but still persists with the same story 
"I'm fine Benji!"
I can tell he's being stubborn and I'm not going to get an answer out of him anytime soon so I back down.
My stomach growls, telling me the waffle did not satisfy my needs.
I stroll back into the kitchen this time finding Count Chocula acceptable.
When I come back into the living room The T. V is on and Joel is looking straight at it, but he isn't watching it.
I'm starting to become worried about Joel.
Not even a blink when I wave my hand in front of his face.
I pick up the remote, turn off the T. V and grab Joel by both shoulders.
    
                ***Joel's P.O.V***
He turns me toward him and I have no choice but to look straight into his eyes.
"Joel I know something is wrong and don't you dare say that there isn't"
"Look Benji there is something wrong but it's something I'd prefer not to discuss with you."
 
"But Joel were twins!" 
"So?"
"So you can tell me anything!"
"No, Benj., I can't"
"Yes, you can Joel!"
He looks like he is on the verge of tears.
I hate Keeping things from him, the only other time I did was when Dad was beating me, but Benji ended up finding out anyway.
I just shake my head sadly and whisper" no".
He sighs and goes back to the kitchen table with his bowl of cereal.
I watch as he eats.
There is milk dripping down the side of his mouth.
It almost looks like......
Shaking my head vigorously I try to rid myself of these thoughts.
But I just can't stop the natural effects of attraction.
I growl in frustration, causing Benji to look up at me.
Our eyes lock and I can feel him prying at the locked door that I have put up.
I am forced to turn away, he can never know my deepest darkest secret.
The only thing I can think of is to run upstairs t escape my brother's sight.
Kicking our bedroom door open and then shut behind me I jump onto my bed.
It's so soft all of the sudden, so much more inviting than the rest of the world.
I look through the pile of shit until I find my CD player.
Soon enough the sound of silverchair's anthem for 2000 is ringing through my ears.
My stomach is growling, I wish I had some breakfast, or lunch since we just woke up and its 1:00 now.
Oh well we should be having supper in a couple of hours.
I'll wait until then, I dare not risk my brother finding out.
He won't try anything with my mother at the table, he wouldn't want me to get in trouble.
 
 
I listen to the whole rancid album and the whole nofx album so about an hour and a half has gone by.
I think Benji Kinda  figured out that I wanted to be alone.
That or he went out with his new pal Tony.
Yea I'm going to g with the second one.
If it seems I'm jelious of Tony it's because I am, Benji Spends more time with him and it hurts.
I'm snapped out of my thoughts when I hear my mother calling my name.
"Joel!" She hollers again.
"Coming!" I reply so she doesn't explode.
"What do you need Momma?"
"Set the table"
"Why?" "It's only 2:30"
"I Know that!" 
"Just do as you're told"
 
"Done"
"Good boy" she says giving me a pat on the head just to make fun of me.
"Why are we eating so early?"
"You're father won't be home until late tonight and Benjiman is eating over Tony's house."
 
Tony
Gotta love it
I guess he wasn't as worried about me as he seemed.
Digging into the mashed potatoes that were just slopped on my plat I realise these are the potatoes from two nights ago.
She must not have had time to go shopping.
